.TH git-daft-skill-install 1  "git-daft-skill-install 1.23.1" 
.SH NAME
git\-daft\-skill\-install \- Install or update the agent skill for Claude Code
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBgit\-daft\-skill\-install\fR [\fB\-\-project\fR] [\fB\-\-dir\fR] [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Writes the agent skill embedded in this daft binary (the repository\*(Aqs
SKILL.md, skill name `daft\-worktree\-workflow`) into a skills directory,
creating parent directories as needed.
.PP
The embedded skill is version\-matched to the binary by construction, so
re\-running the command after upgrading daft is also the update path:
install == update. An existing copy is always overwritten unless it is
already identical. The command is non\-interactive and never touches the
network.
.PP
By default the skill lands in Claude Code\*(Aqs user\-global skills directory
(~/.claude/skills/daft\-worktree\-workflow/SKILL.md). Use \-\-project to
install into the current worktree\*(Aqs .claude/skills/ instead (commit it to
share the skill with everyone who clones the repo), or \-\-dir to target
another agent\*(Aqs skills root; the daft\-worktree\-workflow folder is always
created inside the chosen root, because the folder name is what agents
resolve the skill by.
.PP
`git daft doctor` reports when an installed copy is stale relative to the
running binary, and `git daft doctor \-\-fix` rewrites it with the same
content this command installs.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-project\fR
Install into the current worktree\*(Aqs .claude/skills/ instead of ~/.claude/skills
.TP
\fB\-\-dir\fR \fI<PATH>\fR
Install under this skills root (for agents other than Claude Code)
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress the result line
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Show detailed progress
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH VERSION
v1.23.1
